<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="84d2b1152e98cb77a826b3278db9feed" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Lee Clarke&#39;s V Card - Padme v<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.92)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175'>Scott "CRingwell" Lingrell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> December 27, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> First off let’s have a little information about me because I’m guessing that most of you don’t know who I am. I’ve been playing Star Wars since about DS*II and I live in Canberra (capital city of Australia, yes, it’s not Sydney) where there’s always been an active play group. Some of you might’ve met me at worlds this year, I went there to play Lord of the Rings TCG but got in a little SW CCG gaming as well. I was the tall Aussie guy that came 2nd in the LotR Worlds. <br />
CanCon is Canberra’s annual gaming convention held in January each year and this year the Australian Star Wars CCG Championships were held there, I was lucky enough to win that and so got to design a V Card. <br />
<br />
Seeing as Natalie Portman is hot and there’s pretty much only one deck you can base around Padme at the moment I thought I’d give the community a few more options. <br />
<br />
So I bring you Padme Naberrie V: <br />
<br />
•Padmé Naberrie (V) 3 <br />
CHARACTER - REPUBLIC [Virtual Set 11] <br />
POWER 3 ABILITY 4 FORCE-SENSITIVE <br />
Text: P1. Each non-Jedi Skywalker is defense value and destiny +2. Twice per game, may / a non-Jedi Skywalker. At end of opponent’s turn, opponent loses 1 Force for each Skywalker at a battleground (reduce total by 1 if Vader on table). <br />
DEPLOY 3 FORFEIT 6 <br />
Original concept by Lee Clarke, CanCon 2005 <br />
11•12 <br />
<br />
So first off when I came up with this card Episode III had just been released so I thought it’d be cool to make her relate to that movie in some aspects. Twice per game uploading a Skywalker is cool and I thought it was kinda funny. <br />
<br />
Stats are pretty obvious, I really wanted her to have four ability as I figured she gave birth to Luke and Leia so she’s gotta have something going on there with the force. This went through a fair bit of discussion back and forth with the designers who thought she only deserved 3 ability. Eventually, seeing as how a couple of other Padme personas have 4 ability this persona got 4 too. <br />
<br />
I wanted to continue the Skywalker theme of the card and in the current meta of drop-bash-forfeit, wash-rinse-repeat I wanted to encourage players to keep some characters on the table a bit longer. So I knew I wanted her to give a bonus for having out skywalkers. I thought about adding to destiny draws or retrieving force but in the end settled on the lose force text she has now because it sort of mirrors what Hunt Down does and in a way Padme is sort of responsible for Vader’s anger. In my first iteration of the card she caused a bit more force loss and vader reduced it by more but for balance reasons it was toned back to what you see now. At one point she also uploaded Uncontrollable Fury but that text was deemed a little too powerful. <br />
<br />
The pilot icon was a good idea from the design team and makes her a bit more versatile, it also fitted well with the Episode III theme. <br />
<br />
So in the end we came up with a Padme that I think does well in bringing the story of hiding the twins from Vader to the game. <br />
<br />
There are a few pretty obvious deck designs for Padme. There are stacks of mains/toys decks she can be used in, and I think a Careful Planning V Slave Quarters deck is inevitable. I think there’s also potential for an interesting Hidden Base deck. She will naturally fit easily into TRM or Endor Mains decks as well. I can’t wait to see what other cool ideas everybody can come up with for her. <br />
<br />
As soon as somebody causes 5 force loss in a single turn with her I want to hear about it <br />
